            . I work with Mr. Atkinson, who is a <rs id="t18151206-16-viclabel85" type="occupation">butcher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18151206-16-victim185 t18151206-16-viclabel85"></join>, and lives in <placeName id="t18151206-16-crimeloc86">High street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18151206-16-crimeloc86" type="placeName" value="High street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18151206-16-crimeloc86" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18151206-16-off83 t18151206-16-crimeloc86"></join>. I was minding my shop on the 17th of November, and the prisoner at the bar came and took a loin of mutton from the stall, and wrapped it up under her cloak; I immediately laid hold of her, and took the mutton from under her cloak; and told her she must go to the Compter. She then said, she only took it in a joke. I told her that would not do, for she had taken a loin of mutton on the Wednesday before, and had been let off; and she had robbed several butcher's shops in the neighbourhood. I accordingly sent for a constable, and had her taken into custody. The mutton would not keep.</p>
